    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="147"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the Ambassador in
                        Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d147fn1">Sent to the White House, apparently via
                        military channels; forwarded to the Department of State; and forwarded
                        further by the Department, in telegram 904, November 20, 1943, 7 p.m., to
                        the Legation at Ankara, marked “Secret” and “U. S. Urgent”.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tunis</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-20">20 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From the President to Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_SLA1"
                        >Steinhardt</persName>.</p>
                <p>Please tell President <persName corresp="#p_II1">Inonu</persName> I have landed
                    safely in North Africa <pb facs="0193" n="101" xml:id="pg_101"/> and that I
                    would greatly welcome him. I cannot make my plans until Monday morning<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d147fn2">November 22, 1943.</note> but will advise you at that
                        time.<note n="3" xml:id="d147fn3">For <persName corresp="#p_RFD1"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>’s next message to <persName corresp="#p_SLA1"
                            >Steinhardt</persName>, see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_386">p. 386</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
